Prince Harry spoke with US journalist Hoda Kotb earlier this week, while attending the Invictus Games at The Hague. During the candid chat, the Duke of Sussex opened up about his meeting with the Queen, which took place last week when he and his wife Meghan stopped at Windsor Castle on their way to The Netherlands. And he boasted about having a special relationship with the 95-year-old sovereign, as he said the Queen can talk to him about things she doesn't tell others. He said: "We have a really special relationship, we talk about things that she can't talk about with anybody else." THIS LIVE BLOG IS NOW CLOSED - READ COVERAGE BELOW...